30/09/2004
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- International prosecutors have indicted six ethnic Albanians for the death of a Serb man and the beating of his mother during the mid-March rios in Kosovo. 
Thomas Monaghan, the province's director of justice and former FBI officer, told reporters Wednesday that more indictments will follow.
In other news, new deputy chief of UNMIK, Ambassador Lawrence G. 
Rossin, arrived in Pristina on Wednesday (29 September). 
He replaces Charles Brayshaw, whose mandate expired.(Tanjug, KosovaLive, Reuters, AFP - 29/09/04)
